N.Y. Attorney General to Prosecute Corruption, N.Y. Times Says

-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 
2011-05-23T04:08:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/n-y-attorney-general-to-prosecute-corruption-n-y-times-says.html
New York Attorney General  Eric
Schneiderman  has obtained powers to criminally prosecute
corruption involving public spending, the New York Times
reported, citing an agreement with State Comptroller Thomas
DiNapoli.  Schneiderman’s office will work with DiNapoli’s
investigators and auditors examing legislative earmarks, state
pensions and government contracts who will refer any finding
from joint investigations to the attorney general for criminal
prosecution, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
